content: I don't possess the latest or specific data. however, according to reports, the healthcare and social services industry in sydney has been growing significantly, with demand for services being driven by factors such as an ageing population and an increasing prevalence of chronic diseases. some of the specific services in demand within the industry include aged care services, mental health services, disability services, allied health services such as physiotherapy and occupational therapy, and general medical services such as gps and specialist medical practitioners. the industry also employs a broad range of health professionals, such as nurses, doctors, and allied health workers, who provide services in both public and private sectors.
